body:
**Library verision: Android 4.2.2**

**Issue:**
LottieCompositionFactory.taskCache caused memory leak

**Here is the code in class 'LottieCompositionFactory':**


    private static LottieTask<LottieComposition> cache(@Nullable final String cacheKey, 
    Callable<LottieResult<LottieComposition>> callable) {
        final LottieComposition cachedComposition = cacheKey == null ? null : 
        LottieCompositionCache.getInstance().get(cacheKey);
        if (cachedComposition != null) {
            return new LottieTask(new Callable<LottieResult<LottieComposition>>() {
                public LottieResult<LottieComposition> call() {
                    return new LottieResult(cachedComposition);
                }
            });
        } else if (cacheKey != null && taskCache.containsKey(cacheKey)) {
            return (LottieTask)taskCache.get(cacheKey);
        } else {
            


            // problem is here!
            LottieTask<LottieComposition> task = new LottieTask(callable);
            // LottieTask may has been executed, because its constructor send it to a Executor
            
            if (cacheKey != null) {
                // listener callback will not be called, because before it was added to LottieTask, LottieTask has been executed
                
               task.addListener(new LottieListener<LottieComposition>() {
                    public void onResult(LottieComposition result) {
                        LottieCompositionFactory.taskCache.remove(cacheKey);
                    }
                });
                task.addFailureListener(new LottieListener<Throwable>() {
                    public void onResult(Throwable result) {
                        LottieCompositionFactory.taskCache.remove(cacheKey);
                    }
                });
                taskCache.put(cacheKey, task);
            }

            return task;
        }
    }

LottieTask maybe executed before 'task.addListener()' because LottieTask will be executed in its constructor method. Sometimes our ui thread will be blockedï¼Œand this problem occurs
